From: Mariusz Kozlowski <mk@lab.zgora.pl>
Date: Sat, 20 Nov 2010 12:03:07 +0000
Patch-mainline: yes
References: FATE#306586
Subject: [PATCH] btrfs: make 1-bit signed fileds unsigned

Fixes these sparse warnings:
fs/btrfs/ctree.h:811:17: error: dubious one-bit signed bitfield
fs/btrfs/ctree.h:812:20: error: dubious one-bit signed bitfield
fs/btrfs/ctree.h:813:19: error: dubious one-bit signed bitfield

Signed-off-by: Mariusz Kozlowski <mk@lab.zgora.pl>
Signed-off-by: Chris Mason <chris.mason@oracle.com>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.cz>
---
 fs/btrfs/ctree.h |    6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/fs/btrfs/ctree.h
+++ b/fs/btrfs/ctree.h
@@ -807,9 +807,9 @@ struct btrfs_block_group_cache {
 	int extents_thresh;
 	int free_extents;
 	int total_bitmaps;
-	int ro:1;
-	int dirty:1;
-	int iref:1;
+	unsigned int ro:1;
+	unsigned int dirty:1;
+	unsigned int iref:1;
 
 	int disk_cache_state;
 
